Good! I found that `nfapi_tl_t` is defined as:

```c
typedef struct {
	uint16_t tag;
	uint16_t length;
} nfapi_tl_t;
```

So the `length` field is indeed a `uint16_t`, which means it can only hold values up to 65535 (UINT16_MAX). The problem described in the PR is that when the packed data exceeds 65,535 bytes, the pointer subtraction result gets truncated when assigned to this `uint16_t` field.

